6. You are preparing to launch an application that will be hosted on a set of EC2 instances. This application needs some software installation and some OS packages need to be updated during the first launch. What is the best way to achieve this when you launch the EC2 Instances?

Connect to each EC2 Instance using SSH, then install the required software and update your OS package manually
Write a Bash Script that installs the required software and updates to your OS, then contact AWS Support and provide them with the script. They will run it on your EC2 instances at launch
Write a Bash User script that installs the required software and updates to your OS, then use this script in EC2 User Data when you launch your EC2 Instances 

